article.headline: Texas Arlington 119, Oral Roberts 29
article.story:
TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Seven players scored in double digits and
Oral Roberts head coach Jerry Finkbeiner notched his 300th career
win as ORU defeated Bacone 119-29 Saturday.

The Golden Eagles (1-2) set team records for points, fewest
points allowed, field-goal percentage (70.8), fewest field-goals
allowed (10), lowest opponent field-goal percentage (20.4) and
margin of victory against the NAIA Lady Warriors (1-8).

Elisha Turek led all scorers with 21 points and added seven
rebounds, three steals and two blocks.

Sophomore guard Leah Cannon turned in her second straight game
with 17 points and 15 assists, tying the single-game assists mark
she broke in Tuesday's home loss to Texas-Arlington.

The Golden Eagles led 59-14 at the half on the strength of 74.2
percent shooting.
